---
title: Banh Mi Pork Burgers with Pickled Veggie Slaw, Sriracha Mayo & Garlic Potato Wedges
description: Tonight’s dinner features a favorite Vietnamese sub with a twist: pickled veggies and fresh herbs are piled between potato buns for a banh mi-inspired sandwich, burger-style! Pork patties are infused with citrusy ponzu and aromatic ginger, then topped with a cilantro-lime slaw and generous swipe of spicy chili mayo. Add a heap of garlicky potato wedges on the side, then prepare for total taste bud takeover.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/60ae4e6491db34359f402ff0-ee7df634.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/banh-mi-pork-burgers-60ae4e6491db34359f402ff0-0fe4bf60.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
nutrition:
  calories: 930 kcal
  fat: 48 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 91 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1100 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/banh-mi-pork-burgers-60ae4e6491db34359f402ff0
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Asian
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice 
@Persian cucumber{1} crosswise into rounds. Trim, peel, and grate 
@carrot{3%ounce} on the largest holes of a #box grater{}. Roughly chop 
@cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Halve @lime{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the 
@red onion{1} (use the rest as you like). Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll 
use the rest later), a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{to taste}, 
and @pepper{to taste}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, in a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, carrot, half the 
cilantro, juice from half the lime, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and as much sliced onion 
as you like. (For 4 servings, use juice from whole lime and @sugar{2%teaspoon} 
instead.) Season with a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and pepper. Set aside to pickle.

While potatoes roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with 
@sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

In a second medium bowl, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, ginger, 
@ponzu sauce{12%milliliters}, remaining cilantro, remaining garlic powder, 
@sugar{1%teaspoon}, and @salt{1/4%tsp}. (For 4 servings, use 2 tsp sugar and ½ 
tsp salt.) Form mixture into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider 
than a burger bun.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add patties and 
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

While patties cook, halve and toast @potato buns{2}. TIP: For a deeper flavor, 
toast in pan used for patties over medium heat.

Spread as much Sriracha mayo as you like onto cut sides of bottom buns. Fill buns 
with patties and some pickled veggie slaw.

Divide burgers between plates; serve with garlic potato wedges and remaining 
pickled veggie slaw on the side, with any remaining Sriracha mayo as a dipper.